weekly_top_story.headline: House and Senate Adjourn Without Extending Enhanced ACA Premium Tax Credits, Leaving Millions at Risk of Premium Increases
weekly_top_story.summary: Congress failed to extend the enhanced Affordable Care Act premium tax credits set to expire at year-end, potentially causing premiums to double for millions and leading to 10 million losing coverage by 2034 amid broader 2025 policy shifts like the OBBB's $1.06 trillion cuts.

stories.headline: ACA Deadline Looming | Dec. 23, 2025 | News 19 at 6 p.m.
stories.summary: Expanded ACA subsidies expire at the end of 2025 without congressional extension, driving significantly higher premiums in 2026 and threatening access for millions of insured individuals.
